From 6bf08313b1069cf4129cd408bb5449be7ce244ad Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: regksem <regksem@tuta.io>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 14:38:39 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] Add Geyser/Floodgate (Bedrock) anti-bot exemption

Geyser proxies Bedrock players to the proxy as ordinary Java connections,
so the connection-level anti-bot and anti-exploit checks produce false
positives for them. Add net.regksem.xwaterfall.antibot.BedrockDetector,
which recognises such connections via Geyser's local pipeline handler,
Floodgate's channel marker (read once by reflection) and an optional
trusted-address list, and skips the gating checks for them:

- handshake protocol gating and direct-IP blocking;
- login name pattern, per-IP cap, reconnect firewall and join-rate counting;
- the liveness (ClientSettings deadline) check;
- the single-packet size cap in HandlerBoss.

In-game limits (chat/command spam, tab-complete length) still apply. Gated by
antibot.bedrock.exempt (default true) with antibot.bedrock.trusted-addresses in
xwaterfall.yml; re-resolved on /xwaterfall antibot reload.

